<!DOCTYPE html>
<html dir="ltr" lang="en-US">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title><%= html_title yield(:page_title) %></title>
  <%= csrf_meta_tag %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'home' %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'jquery' %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'rails' %>
  <%= open_id_delegation_link_tags(enki_config[:open_id_delegation, :server], enki_config[:open_id_delegation, :delegate]) if enki_config[:open_id_delegation] %>
  <%= yield(:head) %>
</head>
<body onload="window.defaultStatus='Insomnia Consulting: Software Development Consulting';" >

  <div id="container">
    <div id="intro">
      <div id="pageHeader"><h1><a href="<%= root_url %>"><%= enki_config[:title] %></a></h1>
      </div>
      <div id="preamble">
	<h3><span>Welcome</span></h3>
	<p class="p1"><span>Insomnia Consulting is a software development company which strives to meet the needs of smaller companies and startups.</span></p>
	<p>Over the years, we've noticed that a business has limited choices when it comes to developing software.  They can hire fulltime IT employees, employ an expensive consulting company, or try to deal with individual programmers.</p>
	<p>All these options bring complications.  Whether it's a long-term labor commitment, a short-term, drain on cash, or a reliance on a single individual.</p>
	<p>Insomnia Consulting addresses this by maintaining a pool of freelance developers who, because they are working in their freetime, will usually work at a reduced rate for "extra" cash.  And.. because your contact is with Insomnia, you'll always have a company to rely on and manage the transition between programmers.</p>
	
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="navigation">

<div id="linklist">
<div id="linklist2">
	<h2>Contact</h2>
<div id="lselect"
<ul>
  <li>Phone : 724.398.1023</li>
  <li>Email : info@insomnia-consulting.org
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="linklist">
<div id="linklist2">
        <h2>Pages</h2>
<div id="lselect"

        <ul>
          <% page_links_for_navigation.each do |link| -%>
            <li><%= link_to(link.name, link.url) %></li>
          <% end -%>
        </ul>
        <% unless category_links_for_navigation.empty? -%>
          <h2>Categories</h2>
          <ul>
            <% category_links_for_navigation.each do |link| -%>
              <li><%= link_to(link.name, link.url) %></li>
            <% end -%>
          </ul>
        <% end -%>
        <form method="get" id="sform" action="http://www.google.com/search">
          <div>
            <h2><label for="q">Search</label></h2>

            <input type="text" id="q" value="" name="q">
            <input type="hidden" name="sitesearch" value="<%= enki_config[:url] %>">
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>

      <div id="footer"><%= enki_config[:title] %> &#169; <%= enki_config[:author, :name] %>. Valid <a href="http://validator.w3.org/check?uri=referer">HTML5</a> and <%= link_to "ATOM", "http://feedvalidator.org/check.cgi?url=#{enki_config[:url]}/posts.atom" %>. Powered by <a href="http://www.enkiblog.com" title="A Ruby on Rails blogging app for the fashionable developer">Enki</a>.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>

